                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Cuban Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-09-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 147.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 21st instant, in which you quote your government’s telegram
                    expressing its deep regret at the deplorable outrage perpetrated on the American
                    consulate at Cienfuegos, and renew the assurances previously given that no
                    effort will be spared to punish the offender.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to say that the good will thus exhibited by the Cuban Government
                    is highly appreciated by this government.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
